@startuml nightlight_backends
!include dark-theme.puml
' Revised 2026-05-13: applied audit_23/Wave-1-fix amendments
title Night-light dispatch - two live backends, registry as the source of truth

[Caller (UI / hotkey / env curve)] as CALLER
[NightLightProvider\n(static facade,\n_lastResolvedBackend cache)] as NLP
[AppSettings\nNightLightFallbackMode] as MODE

package "Backend resolution" $TINT_BLUE {
  [ResolveBackend\n(switch on mode)] as RESOLVE
}

package "Live backends" $TINT_AMBER {
  [Backend.SettingsHandler\nNightLightSettingsHandler] as B_SH
  [Backend.Registry\nNightLightRegistry] as B_REG
  [Backend.None\n(unsupported)] as B_NONE
}

package "SettingsHandler write path (kelvin only)" $TINT_PURPLE {
  [NightLightCloudStore\n(RVA-resolved, MTA-init)] as CS
  [BlueLightSingleton\n::SetTargetColorTemperature\n::SetPreviewColorTemperatureChanges] as SING
  [SHTaskPool\nSaveSettingsAsync (tag 258)] as SHTP
  [ICloudStore::Save\n(succeeds on SHTaskPool thread)] as CSAVE
  [NightLightSettingsHandler\n._deferredRegistryTimer\n(System.Threading.Timer,\nNightLightUIHandleryRegistryEnforceDelayMs;\nmirror of NightLightRegistry._resendTimer)] as SHDEF
}

package "Registry write path (kelvin only)" $TINT_TEAL {
  [SETTINGS blob\n(CloudStore Bond CB v1)] as REGSET
  [STATE blob\n(field 0 enabled, field 20 FILETIME)] as REGSTATE
  [RegNotifyChangeKeyValue\nwait between writes] as REGNOTIFY
}

[BlueLightReductionService\n(broker live filter)] as BROKER

CALLER --> NLP : SetStrength / SetEnabled\nToggle / Reapply / IsEnabled\nGetStrength
MODE  ..> NLP  : Changed event\nInvalidateBackendCache only when\nNightLightFallbackMode actually moves\n(other AppSettings.Changed fires are no-ops)
NLP   --> RESOLVE : first call /\non mode change

RESOLVE --> B_SH   : mode == SettingsHandler\n&& CloudStore.IsSupported()
RESOLVE --> B_REG  : mode == Auto / Registry / GammaRamp\n(Registry.IsSupported())
RESOLVE --> B_NONE : mode == SettingsHandler\nbut RVA init failed\n(no silent downgrade)

note right of RESOLVE
  GammaRamp is a hidden enum value with
  no implementation - the resolver folds it
  into the Registry branch.
  Auto is a legacy XML-compat value, also
  treated as Registry.
  Default for new installs is SettingsHandler.
end note

B_SH  --> CS : SetStrength(percent)\nSaveSettingsKelvinAsync
B_SH  --> B_REG : Get / IsEnabled\nSetEnabled / Toggle\n(Registry is the read+toggle owner)
B_SH  --> SHDEF : ArmDeferredRegistryWrite\n(every SetStrength / SetEnabled / Toggle)
SHDEF --> B_REG : OnDeferredRegistryTimerFired\n-> NightLightRegistry.SetStrength(latest)\n+ RefreshStateFileTime\n(callback wrapped in try/catch - M-11)

CS --> SING : 1) SetTargetColorTemperature(kelvin)\n2) SetPreviewColorTemperatureChanges(1)\n3) SetPreviewColorTemperatureChanges(0)
SING --> SHTP : queue SaveSettingsAsync\nbetween steps
SHTP --> CSAVE : on SHTaskPool worker thread
CSAVE --> REGSET : ICloudStore writes\nSETTINGS blob
CS    .> REGNOTIFY : await one-shot notify\nbefore next step

B_REG --> REGSET : SetStrength: WriteSettingsBlob\nspaced bracket (IsDragging C2 46 01)\nstep 1: kelvin, dragging=false\nstep 2: kelvin, dragging=true\nstep 3: kelvin, dragging=false
B_REG --> REGSTATE : Toggle / SetEnabled:\nflip enabled marker (10 00)\n+ refresh FILETIME (C6 14)
B_REG --> REGNOTIFY : await IssueWithSaveNotifyAsync\nbetween bracket steps

REGSET   --> BROKER : CloudCacheInvalidator fires\nfor CloudStore-API saves only;\nraw writes propagate via\nRegNotifyChangeKeyValue
REGSTATE --> BROKER : FILETIME bump = real transition\n(state save chain)
CSAVE    --> BROKER : version-counter bump\ntriggers OnBlueLightReductionSettingsChange

note bottom of CS
  History:
   - direct ICloudStore::Save from our
     thread fails 0x80070490
     (CloudStorePartitionSet::GetPartitionInfo
      NOT_FOUND).
   - riding SHTaskPool's worker context is
     what makes Save succeed.
   - SHTaskPool dedups tag 258, but each task
     captures the current kelvin at queue
     time, so latest-wins still lands.
   - RVAs cached per DLL FileVersion in
     nightlight_known_rvas.xml; PDB resolver
     is the slow-path fallback.
end note

note bottom of B_REG
  Spaced-bracket trick (registry-only):
  the IsDragging false->true edge triggers
  ColorTemperatureControl::fb3daf, which
  calls ApplyTemperatureChangeToMonitorsImmediate
  unconditionally - bypasses the wedged
  +36 inflight gate that drops kelvin-only
  writes on 24H2 / 26200.

  Belt-and-suspenders: a single shared
  System.Threading.Timer re-fires the last
  bracket NightLightUIHandleryRegistryEnforceDelayMs after
  the most recent enqueue (one-shot per
  quiet period, no infinite loop). The same
  constant is the dueTime for the
  SettingsHandler backend's
  _deferredRegistryTimer settle-write.

  Both timer callbacks now wrapped in
  try/catch (M-11) so background-thread
  exceptions cannot tear down the process.

  CancelPendingResend is a public method
  on both NightLightRegistry and
  NightLightSettingsHandler. The zero-trap
  fix (M-07) calls it on BOTH backends
  before SetEnabled(false), so a pending
  resend can never resurrect a non-zero
  strength after the user just toggled off.

  PulseApply (toggle off then on) is kept
  as a manual recovery primitive only;
  the FILETIME bump in SetStrength normally
  makes a pulse unnecessary.
end note

note right of NLP
  Reads always go through Registry, even
  on the SettingsHandler backend - the
  registry blobs are the OS source of truth.

  EnsureNonZeroStrengthBeforeEnable:
  toggling on at strength 0 silently restores
  AppSettings.NightLightLastNonZeroStrength
  first, otherwise the user sees no visible
  change.

  TurnOffNightLightAtZeroStrength:
  setting strength to 0 auto-disables when
  the option is on.
end note

@enduml
